A home loan provides two major tax benefits under the old regime: **Section 24(b)** allows deduction of up to ₹2 lakh per year on home loan interest for a self-occupied property, and **Section 80C** allows up to ₹1.5 lakh on principal repayment. Together, these can save ₹1–1.5 lakh in tax annually.
